Tests for the 'straight' concept.

These are two danceable sequences.

Several examples from www.mit.edu/~tech-squares/resources/cotm/9202.html

Some other (less elegant) openings:
 - heads pair off ; sides truck ; straight butterfly cross chain thru
 - heads slide thru ; straight cross concentric catch 1
 - heads pair off ; swing and straight mix (?)

sdr> /program = C4
C4
sdr> heads pair off
| 4B>  3G<  3B>  2G<
| 
| 4G>  1B<  1G>  2B<
sdr> /// sd calls this, "swing the gamut but [STRAIGHT cut the diamond]"
sdr> finally straight swing the gamut
| 4B>  1B>
| 
| 2G>  1G>
| 
| 3G<  4G<
| 
| 3B<  2B<
sdr> straight mix
| 3G>  4G>
|
| 3B>  4B>
|
| 2B<  1B<
|
| 2G<  1G<
sdr> straight switch the line
| 3B<  4B<
|
| 2G>  3G>
|
| 1G<  4G<
|
| 2B>  1B>
sdr> straight trade the wave
| 1G>  4G>
|
| 4B<  1B<
|
